<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n40102a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40102a">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40102a"> 102(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ sweet of soul</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">So he perished and fared to Jahannam-fire and the dwelling-place dire. Even so it is said of books:&mdash;Whoever diggeth for his brother a pit shall himself fall into it and whoever setteth up a snare for his neighbour shall be snared therein.&rdquo; And this much know we anent the Say of Hakyar the Sage, and magnification be to Allah for ever and ever, AMEN. TMT. <small> Richard F. Burton, trans. <a name="RFBS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RFBS"><cite title="source">Supplemental Nights to the Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night with Notes Anthropological and Explanatory</cite></a> (n.d.) xvi.30</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
